# ── Rust / Cargo build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Cargo writes all build output to `target/`. This must never be committed.
# The repo has Cargo workspaces under src/edge-ingress and src/envoy, so
# we ignore both top-level and nested target/ directories.
target/
**/target/
# Per-workspace Cargo state.
**/.cargo-lock
.cargo/
# Cargo intermediate library outputs (defensive; usually inside target/).
*.rlib
*.rmeta
# Debug symbols emitted by some Rust toolchains.
*.pdb
*.dSYM/
# WASM artifacts produced by `cargo build --target wasm32-wasi`. The
# deployable .wasm is published by CI (helm `--set-file wasm.base64=...`),
# not committed to source control.
*.wasm
# NOTE: Cargo.lock is intentionally NOT ignored. We commit it for binary
# crates (edge-ingress) per the official Cargo guidance to make builds
# reproducible. Library-only crates that are published to crates.io would
# typically ignore Cargo.lock, but no crate in this repo is published.

# ── Mesh + cluster bootstrap material (NEVER COMMIT) ──────────────────
# Generated by Phase 7 (Linkerd mesh CA — `step certificate create`) and
# Phase 8 (Vault init / secrets bootstrap). ca.key and issuer.key are the
# LINKERD ROOT and ISSUER PRIVATE KEYS — a single leaked commit forces a
# full mesh re-issue. Vault is the source of truth (written in Phase 8.4);
# the on-disk PEMs are transient and must be `shred -u`'d (the .key files)
# / `rm -f`'d (the .crt files) once Phase 8.4 completes. Anchored to repo
# root with a leading "/" so legitimate certificate fixtures under
# helm/*/templates/ or tests/* are unaffected.
/ca.crt
/ca.key
/issuer.crt
/issuer.key

# Vault init bundle (5 unseal keys + root token) and generated-credentials
# bundle from Phase 8.11. The runbook deliberately writes these to $HOME
# (~/vault-init.txt, ~/etradie-<env>-creds.txt) at mode 0600, OUTSIDE the
# repo. These rules are the safety net if an operator runs Phase 3.2 /
# Phase 8.11 with the working dir inside the repo by mistake.
/vault-init.txt
/etradie-prod-creds.txt
/etradie-staging-creds.txt

# Cloudflare Tunnel connector token (captured in Phase 6.1) and the
# short-lived REST API bootstrap token (minted in Phase 6.2.1). Same
# posture as the Vault files: runbook keeps them at
# ~/cloudflare-<env>-tunnel-token.txt and
# ~/.cloudflare-<env>-api-token.txt OUTSIDE the repo; these rules catch
# the case where an operator drops them inside the repo by mistake. The
# tunnel token is long-lived (its lifetime is the tunnel's lifetime); the
# API token is 48h TTL and must be `shred -u`'d after Phase 6.
/cloudflare-*-tunnel-token.txt
/.cloudflare-*-api-token.txt
*.zip
